1FE770DD4EC6AF9B22BAA6847D9F115A: Initiate by Jumping while in air.

Dialogue.4DC5C3A640C39988EA33FB8437D20132_8E916AD: And if it doesn't work... Well, we had some laughs, right?
Dialogue.467C7B00453735998118519167D903B7_8E916AD: Bad news. Galactus? Definitely out to get you.
Dialogue.4A74D41540D726BE7CAD338489344D9F_8E916AD: By my calculations if Galactus keeps absorbing the Zero Point at that rate, uh, we'll all be looking at a full reality collapse in--
Dialogue.9CD9C6B5494B216829A42E823B3F41BB_8E916AD: Cute. You know, I was hoping we'd have an excuse to try out the Battle Bus's laser cannons.
Dialogue.C10ABE6A4AC003DE80380A85E224FB5D_8E916AD: Doesn't matter. You know, the point is we gotta move.
Dialogue.306D74464701456818BBD695BE549C6C_8E916AD: Driver, we're taking you up his arm.
Dialogue.5F7EC0BC458A61DB6C413EA21AF655E7_BADBCF5: Fear not. I shall divert your strange War Wagon!
Dialogue.B4516A744BDE57A1FE0A7BB49C25304F_8E916AD: Good news, I got the stereo working.
Dialogue.1C3D576F4258C0F647BB2F8DD0B5A002_8E916AD: Hey, Blondie! Got a bus over here that's getting a little hot.
Dialogue.9F4BAD5B48993FD07744398EA858DF56_8E916AD: How's the handling on that thing? I didn't really get the chance to test it, eh, so it might be a little... uh... like a bus. Bus-like.
Dialogue.62E3073444B8D7B0B36756AC62E84564_8E916AD: I admire that enthusiasm, but again you are driving a bomb so let's be careful out there.
Dialogue.93F4F0714754FDD3408F96BE2C73E94F_8E916AD: I hacked your time loop thingy, made a few billion Battle Bus clones, and then turned them all into very powerful bombs.
Dialogue.43FFA9DE471F04543D09DDAFD70ABF85_8E916AD: If everything goes right, it'll open a portal and send him back where he came from.
Dialogue.B03B66854FAA62D31777F2AA91C6A366_8E916AD: If this works, it's Return to Sender for all of us.
Dialogue.ED2729B34A923190BA381DB23F0BBDAB_94CA28D: Just get me up there, bub!
Dialogue.FDE08C224F22E28C0E5D0AA0A77374F6_8E916AD: Just keep flying north and try not to let it freak you out. Okay?
Dialogue.8B11A63144892B42B51BE69639BFE83C_8E916AD: Look at that! You're a natural! Stay on target and don't explode.
Dialogue.9C4DD14C463E66986C1B33AD9D3742DC_8E916AD: Looks like he's taking the bait!
Dialogue.3AF5928D42C911F1A19C28B0E3687862_8E916AD: My buddy sent me this new track that his band wrote. I think they might just make it someday.
Dialogue.DEB596954FFC66924BF00F90D2596FD3_8E916AD: Oh! Almost forgot. Your lasers won't do much to the big guy, but they should make short work of those drones.
Dialogue.D821976D48AEED8127E1369377931AAC_8E916AD: Okay, so I took the liberty of tinkering with your reality a bit. It's really no big deal, you can thank me later.
Dialogue.D75CBCA64EA6363068B8FFB9A524C4F5_8E916AD: Okay, this is funny. Don't panic but I think he spotted you.
Dialogue.A5E255474FD88B279E106D8CE02020D7_8E916AD: Oooh! He's getting right to it! Okay. Energy readings are going berserk.
Dialogue.CE39A7044DB79DE10D1727A849947FB7_8E916AD: Sorry if it's getting hot in there. Had to remove the AC to, uh, fit all the, uh, Unstable Molecules.
Dialogue.2300017545FB392F53A982B770F8910E_8E916AD: We gotta stop Galactus from eating the Zero Point.
Dialogue.564325E74997426C9908BC98DA24F465_8E916AD: We need to get Galactus to eat as many buses as possible before he's done with the Zero Point.
Dialogue.9034BAD042F97CB308DCE59E9CFA48E0_8E916AD: We need to get him off the Zero Point now.
Dialogue.F6D061B74DB12B894B6508AE19D14568_8E916AD: What's the point of saving reality if you don't have an awesome soundtrack while you do it?
Dialogue.CBE60356443C95F54B936FBE8A6EDD12_8E916AD: Wow, I am picking up a lot of robots.
Dialogue.9E993D77429E0CA18FA8BDBB78FA651F_8E916AD: Wow. That is really beautiful. Also really bad.
Dialogue.12A9802D4EE643E8DF0C7A815B91304F_8E916AD: Yo, Muttonchops! Think you could, uh, give us a hand?
Dialogue.75E15F674FBAE1A8F084CBAAD50AE6A4_8E916AD: You can drive a Battle Bus, right?
Dialogue.7FB006074CB7C21FC7F8829154F59F51_8E916AD: You look like someone who needs a jetpack.
